Two children have died after a heater exploded in the room they were in Dunnottar Military base east of Johannesburg on Sunday.It is reported that the children aged six and 12 months were left alone upstairs in a room with the electric heater on, while the father and the nanny were downstairs.Captain Johanness Ramphora Police spokesperson stated that both the father and the nanny smelled something burning.&#8220;When they went to investigate they found that the heater had exploded. Both children were killed,&#8221; said Ramphora.The children&#8217;s father was also seriously burned was rushed to the hospital.Ramphora has also indicated that police have opened a case document to investigate what happened.TNA Reporter 